                            <comment id="245593" author="jgmitter" created="Thu, 11 Apr 2019 14:12:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Qian,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The documentation language is a bit cumbersome, but the process is well documented here: &lt;a href=&quot;http://wiki.lustre.org/Lustre_Manual_Changes.&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://wiki.lustre.org/Lustre_Manual_Changes.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;What seems to work best for those not familiar with docbook xml is to first put together the documentation in self-contained MS word document or a single wiki page. &#160;If you have all that self contained, I can help you to translate it to docbook.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks.&lt;br/&gt;
Joe&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="245583" author="qian_wc" created="Thu, 11 Apr 2019 11:39:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Joe,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I will work on it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Btw, what&apos;s the format of the documentation of PCC feature?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Regards,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Qian&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
